{
  "title": "Apprenticeships in Switzerland",
  "story": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "b57b4d7a-ed17-426b-ab12-9ca75b0dab9a",
      "text": "Switzerland has an apprenticeship similarly to Germany and Austria. The educational system is ternar, which is basically [[dual education system]] with mandatory practical courses. The length of an apprenticeship can be 2, 3 or 4 years."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "c2edadb7-a412-4c78-bddb-984e97fad6e7",
      "text": "# Length"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "25bf5787-4cf7-4340-8c4c-30cbb2daed7d",
      "text": "Apprenticeships with a length of 2 years are for persons with weaker school results. The certificate awarded after successfully completing a 2-year apprenticeship is called \"Eidgenössisches Berufsattest\" (EBA) in German and \"Certificato federale di formazione pratica\" (CFP) in Italian."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "1a948a30-6366-4ce3-a39d-22d500f41d5d",
      "text": "Apprenticeship with a length of 3 or 4 years are the most common ones. The certificate awarded after successfully completing a 3 or 4-year apprenticeship is called \"Certificat Fédérale de Capacité\" (CFC ([[:fr:Certificat fédéral de capacité]])),  \"Eidgenössisches Fähigkeitszeugnis\" (EFZ) or \"Attestato federale di capacità\" (AFC)."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "131ef74d-5df0-48df-a2f1-ed858bd84642",
      "text": "Some crafts like Electrician are educated in lengths of 3 and 4 years. In this case, an Electrician with 4 years apprenticeship gets more theoretical background than one with 3 years apprenticeship. Also, but that is easily lost in translation, the profession has a different name."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "71c37bd4-4fb3-4291-bfc0-0c788f6a2923",
      "text": "Each of the over 300 nationwide defined vocational profiles has defined framework - conditions as length of education, theoretical and practical learning goals and certification conditions."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "52fef671-f8fa-423a-bc94-39d7b41c40c7",
      "text": "# Age of the apprentices"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "77d875eb-8e4e-40b8-92f0-915c968f6255",
      "text": "Typically an apprenticeship is started at age of 15 and 18 after finishing general education. Some apprenticeships have a recommend or required age of 18, which obviously leads to a higher average age. There is formally no maximum age, however, for persons above 21 it is hard to find a company due to companies preferring younger ages due to the lower cost of labour."
    }
